cp -rp {dir1/,dir2/,...} destination

	-> only if you're already in the source directory.
	-> -r --> recursive -p --> keep the permissions
implement the same for files but remove -r option.
source: https://askubuntu.com/questions/327282/copying-multiple-specific-files-from-one-folder-to-another#:~:text=The%20syntax%20uses%20the%20cp,no%20spaces%20between%20the%20files.
